The Finnish Meteorological Institute processes its personal data lawfully and transparently. The use of personal data is informed, among other things, by means of privacy notices. The data will only be used for the purpose for which it was originally collected. The Finnish Meteorological Institute shall retain the data for the period specified by law or for as long as necessary.

</p><h2 data-v-2682af5c data-v-2682af5c>Personal Data Request</h2><p data-v-2682af5c data-v-2682af5c>
The data subject has the right to verify their own personal data. The request for personal data can be sent to the Finnish Meteorological Institute's postal address or by e-mail <a href="mailto:kirjaamo@fmi.fi" data-v-2682af5c data-v-2682af5c>kirjaamo@fmi.fi</a>. The data controller only provides personal data to the data subject themselves.
